# Git workflow (Caelus)

`dev` is the canonical work branch. `main` is release-only and is promoted by
the maintainer.

## Rules

- Commit and push work to `dev`. Nothing else by default.
- NEVER commit, push, reset, or force-push to `main`. The maintainer promotes
  `dev` → `main`, or explicitly tells you to. "Promote" / "release" = `main`;
  only then touch `main`, and confirm first.
- Do NOT create feature branches and do NOT open pull requests unless the
  maintainer explicitly asks for one.
- Before every `git push`, verify the current branch is `dev` (or a branch the
  maintainer named this session). If it is `main`, stop.
- A local `pre-push` hook blocks pushes to `main`. Do not bypass it. Promotion
  is the maintainer's call: `CAELUS_ALLOW_MAIN_PUSH=1 git push origin main`.

## When unsure

Ask before any action that changes branch structure (new branches, PRs,
merges, resets, pushes to `main`). Match the existing workflow rather than
introducing a new one.
